===Etymology===
Latin from Greek [[εχίνος]] ''(ekhinos)'', [[hedgehog]].

===Noun===
'''echidna''' (plural: [[echidnas]])
# A small spined [[monotreme]], also known as a [[spiny]] [[anteater]], found in Australia and southern [[New Guinea]].

